text: Cissus adnata is a woody vine species in the genus Cissus found in Asia and Australia. Pallidol is a resveratrol dimer found in C. pallida.Pallidol, a resveratrol dimer from Cissus pallida. Mushtaq A. Khan, Shah G. Nabi, Satya Prakash and Asif Zaman, Phytochemistry, Volume 25, Issue 8, 17 July 1986, Pages 1945-1948, ==References== adnata
title: Cissus adnata
